This article is a presidential proclamation issued by President Barack Obama on May 6, 2010, recognizing and honoring Military Spouse Appreciation Day. The proclamation highlights the important role that military spouses play in supporting and shouldering the responsibilities of their servicemember partners. It acknowledges their contributions to military families and communities, as well as their efforts in caring for wounded warriors and honoring fallen heroes. The proclamation also mentions the commitment of the administration to improving opportunities and quality of life for military spouses, such as increasing compensation, funding for housing and support services, and expanding ground forces to reduce deployment strain. President Obama calls upon the people of the United States to honor military spouses through appropriate ceremonies and activities on May 7, 2010.